This paper is primarily focused on the application of machine learning techniques for malware classification, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically deals with the susceptibility of neural networks to adversarial examples, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a novel dynamic programming obfuscation algorithm, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SI).
